==== SOURCE


https://www.the-scientist.com/news-opinion/ai-decodes-speech-and-hearing-based-on-brain-activity-66213





==== AGENT

Facebook and carried out at the University of California, San Francisco






==== GOAL


AI Decodes Speech and Hearing Based on Brain Activity

==== DATA



training on a limited set of questions and answers



==== METHODS


The study, conducted on three people who had arrays of electrodes temporarily implanted in their brains to monitor their brain activity in preparation for surgery for epilepsy



==== RESULTS

After training on a limited set of questions and answers, a computer model used in the study was able to correctly decode the question a participant heard 76 percent of the time, and the answer that person gave 61 percent of the time, based on the participants’ brain activity.


==== COMMENTS

Facebook's brain-computer interface (BCI) program, outlining  goal to build a non-invasive, wearable device that lets people type by simply imagining themselves talking

